Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.27,0:00:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 6th of March 2021, which is 10 days ago, at the time I'm recording this,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.46,0:00:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a gentleman called Lou Ottens passed away at the age of 94.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.84,0:00:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're a person who watches this channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.94,0:00:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it's more than likely you're already familiar with this fact because
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.58,0:00:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he is the chat credited as being the inventor of the Philips' Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.06,0:00:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to start off by talking about this word "inventor"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.76,0:00:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because to me, it conjures up certain images I'm thinking a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.59,0:00:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like people working away in a lab and look what I've invented, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.23,0:00:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Philips' Compact Cassette was invented what I would consider
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.84,0:00:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of in the modern age, you know late fifties, sixties, that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And things weren't really just one guy at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.82,0:00:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm sure something came out there was just one blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.27,0:00:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Philips' Compact Cassette certainly wasn't one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.92,0:01:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit like saying, that Steve Jobs invented the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.19,0:01:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you wouldn't say that, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.00,0:01:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you search who invented the iPhone, you're not gonna get one name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.15,0:01:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna get, like there's a team that worked on this product for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was kind of, half this idea, half that idea, they put those two things together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.49,0:01:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then changed it and this that on the other era.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.40,0:01:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing with the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.43,0:01:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So Lou Ottens is credited as being the inventor of the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.75,0:01:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think he was particularly happy with that acknowledgement himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.24,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a documentary which came out a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's kind of credited as that in this,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.46,0:01:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see he's not comfortable with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, with his old team.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.86,0:01:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: "Well, it's not really me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.33,0:01:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's a team thing there, were like 40 people working on it at that time."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.50,0:01:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got the designer there, the guy that drew out the cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.01,0:01:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the engineers, all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.44,0:01:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fact is not to take anything away without Lou Ottens
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up with the idea and saying: "Look, this is what we need to work on!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.80,0:01:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Philips won't have worked on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But as far as like "the inventor of it",
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.97,0:01:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, he's kind of the instigator of the project
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop the cassette within Philips.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, even outside Philips, there were loads of other people working on this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, there were other pre-existing products
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you know, predated the Philips' Compact Cassette
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and very much along similar lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not an idea that just came out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.18,0:02:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of having tape inside a cassette or a cartridge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that you didn't have to spool onto a machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way that they went about that was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.40,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,really combining a few things that had gone before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And those things really set out all the groundwork for the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This did it successfully, but the people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that went there first really made this possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.61,0:02:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's look at some of the products that existed before the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to understand what pre-existing technologies there were
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.96,0:02:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that could have influenced the design of the Compact Cassette,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we first of need to know when the compact was being developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was first shown to the public at the end of August 1963.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.62,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which, of course means, that the development precedes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And as far as various things I've read ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he either started as a project in 1960 or 1961.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we just assume 1960 is when it started,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when Lou Ottens walks into his team at Philips
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and says: "You know what, here's what we need to work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Um, fed up tried to spool tape onto a real to real machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's come up with something simpler,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"and in a nice cartridge that's a lot easier to use."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now of course, Philips had a history of reel-to-reel machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is a slightly lighter tape again, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, they had a lot of reel-to-reel tape recorders on the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, there are a couple of products from their own range
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.56,0:03:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that really had a lot of influence on the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One was this. Now this is branded as a Stellaphone from Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was made by Philips.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.72,0:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This uses three inch reels of tape, and this first came out in 1961.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:04:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In a slightly earlier version than this one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.23,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But this older truckload of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which encourages them to continue working on the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.31,0:04:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They probably got some more funding for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on this thing being a big success.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that uses um three inch reels. I've got one here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a little three inch wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than take it off the machine, it's spooled on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, there's plenty of little machines
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.71,0:04:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,out already that use three inch reels of tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of Philips own product use one of those in a cassette already,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and this was prior to that in 1957 or 58, this came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.89,0:04:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out it's probably the end of 57, early 58.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This thing weighs a ton, metal this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's the model number on this? I've just got to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.46,0:04:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, EL3581.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a Philips dictation device.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just looks like another reel-to-reel machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it uses these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.40,0:04:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These are three inch reels again, in a cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.60,0:05:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'd buy them like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.65,0:05:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't have to put your own in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,although you can open them up to put them on another machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Philips' first cassette, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.13,0:05:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Very rudimentary crew, just two reels
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with a hole in these plastic things of the tape going between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're just designed to make, you know, easy snap load, they'd call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were just pop it on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a Philips cassette from 1957.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.68,0:05:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's one thing that predates the Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were some other products that had more of a direct influence on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.98,0:05:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me grab a couple of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now this is more like it, this is a cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Since... Well, it isn't a cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.24,0:05:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a RCA sound tape cartridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.55,0:05:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a promo video for this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it's a film back in the day
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course, it's on YouTube, there was a video though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's from 1958.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:05:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, a lot of the things that you read
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,about the RCA sound tape cartridge, you'll say:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.37,0:06:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh! It came out in 1958."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That promo video, like a lot of things, preceded the launch of the product.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And by quite a bit. I mean, RCA had been working on this for ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but as you'll be aware from watching various videos
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.41,0:06:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about RCA's development of products, they seem to have a failure to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.14,0:06:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, the long development into things,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.37,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they just can't get it out to market properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kind of trip up at that last hurdle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.46,0:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the case with this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,After years of development, it didn't come out until late 1959.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.53,0:06:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a soft launch, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, RCA themselves only had two machines I think, when this thing came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it encouraged some other people, Bell or Bell console, to get on board with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And they like went a bit more all in on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.78,0:06:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so you'll find more machines from other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(And) RCA didn't really back their own product in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They kind of sold it. So it's like a time share or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They sell it off to other people who are buying into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then RCA account "Well, we're not too sure ourselves."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, they really fumbled this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But what this product is? Perhaps I should have started with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quarter inch tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.28,0:07:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, much the same as that Philips thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was stereo, and the machines had auto reverse on some of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it basically, really nice format, sounds alright as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a demo of one of these, it sounded great.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a kind of 1959 product, so definitely out at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Philips is sitting there thinking: "Let's come out with a cassette!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.19,0:07:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a cassette, but this was a a failure in the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Partially due to the kind of lack of,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, enthusiasm from RCA for their own product, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And partially because of the price, in fact, let's go into the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.19,0:07:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's find that, I've got it on somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.49,0:07:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost $300 for one of the RCA machines, that was $2700 today, with inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can understand that not becoming a mass market product.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of nice innovations in this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.17,0:08:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, four track tape, this is the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.02,0:08:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone did four track was for this format
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.08,0:08:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and four track became a familiar thing in home reel-to-reel machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, they slowed the tape speed down to 3.75 inches per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Most tape recorders at the time were running at 7.5 inches per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People were wondering: "Well, will 3.75 and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,four track be good enough for sound quality?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And they proved it was with this and, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,part of that was down to the input from 3M
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.84,0:08:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in developing better formulations of tape for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.28,0:08:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the earlier tapes were quite rough
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and for ready, you need to run them at a fast speed and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe only put two tracks on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to get four tracks and at half the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and still sounding good not too much hiss,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.92,0:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you're developing a formulation, just that kind of pushed that side of the market on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,3M were working on the tape for this for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They were aware of this product going to come out at any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.00,0:08:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now see, we'll have this product, it's going to be massive success in the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So 3M gearing up for this product, and RCA are dragging the heels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:09:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 3M were getting fed up with RCA at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and so, you know, what we're going to launch our own cassette format
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.53,0:09:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,our own tape format, shouldn't call it cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call them cartridge at the time, serve them as a cartridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're going to launch their own cartridge system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.58,0:09:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because they got fed up with RCA, just fumbling and dragging the heels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.80,0:09:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And um, this is it, this is the 3M system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.29,0:09:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This, they were showing off in 1959.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.59,0:09:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it was 1960 and then 61,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually it came out in December 62.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.72,0:09:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think they proved to themselves that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it might not be as easy launching a format as they thought
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.46,0:09:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when they were getting angry with RCA.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.75,0:09:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, the 3M revere cartridge system, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is what made the cassette possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The headline stats for these are identical to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.00,0:09:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They both are at the same speed, 1.875 inches per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.87,0:09:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The tape is an eighth of an inch across.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference was that when the Philips' was launched, it was a mono format.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.39,0:09:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To track one going in either direction, you play that side you play that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just one track.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, similar idea, two-track system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But they use this tracks for stereo, so you've got a bigger reel here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course than you would have in a cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happened with this format is the tape gets pulled out of the cartridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is basically spool one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's spooled up inside the machine, and the tape gets pulled across.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.44,0:10:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're using your two tracks for your stereo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So these were the music format, from the word go stereo music format.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the thing that happened with these (is)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.16,0:10:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the one thing that made the cassette possible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was the proving that you could run a tape at that speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the quality was good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was because 3M being the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.15,0:10:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who created this format again, worked on the formulations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop a new low noise type of formulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.39,0:10:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which was suitable for music at 1.875 inches per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is really the ancestor of the cassette,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.21,0:11:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with a bit of this as well, because that's kind of the design.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.87,0:11:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you add those two things together, and you end up with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, almost. And um, besides that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.36,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there was another format that was on the market as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got that one here, so I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.93,0:11:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,bring up some photos from the Museum of Obsolete Media.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.04,0:11:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so you're looking at the Minifon Attaché.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.82,0:11:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This was first shown off in 1959,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.00,0:11:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but launched in 1960 by the German company Protona, based in Hamburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.80,0:11:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They primarily made kind of spy recorder, type devices or miniature recorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.94,0:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got one of their wire recorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The tape using here is a quarter inch inside this cassette,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's definitely a cassette or cartridge system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that looks similar to the Philips Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And yeah, it came out in 1960, the time when
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.11,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Philips started work on their compact cassette .
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm quite sure that Philips were aware of the existence of the Minifon Attaché.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they weren't developing the cassette in a bubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking at what was out there on the market already,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.37,0:12:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then working on improving upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mentioned that they did specifically look at the RCA Cartridge System,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and indeed, the 3M Revere Wollensak System as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm quite sure that the Minifon Attaché was also in that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But these are perhaps a little bit more famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This one, I'm sure not too many people here have heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.56,0:12:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not well known nowadays, but that's because it wasn't a success in the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.72,0:12:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but what this format then went on to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it developed this tape this eighth of an inch wide tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.66,0:12:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't out before this format.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This higher quality eighth of an inch wide tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which then went on to be used in the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Philips are looking around to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.94,0:12:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,well, what can this cassette have in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were following the Minifon Attaché,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:12:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they're just using quarter inch wide tape which makes your cartridge a certain size.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.84,0:12:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But you get eighth of an inch wide tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.44,0:12:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get a much smaller format,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.83,0:13:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and effectively that is what has happened here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.83,0:13:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gone from 3.75 inches per second with a quarter inch tape
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to 1.875 inches per second with an eighth of an inch tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.40,0:13:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the difference in the size of the cassettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So really, it's the tape that's in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.40,0:13:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the big development that really made the cassette possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I just want to mention why this was not a success again
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if we just go back to prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So in December 1962, they were doing test sales of the system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.19,0:13:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was 450 dollars for a recorder or a player for these cartridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So 450 dollars, 1962, inflation today, 3900 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the tapes are cheaper, but the machine itself costs a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why this wasn't a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So what Philips did and went on to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,use this tape format in a much simpler system.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.75,0:13:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, a much cheaper system (to) manufacture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, the cassettes, relatively cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.01,0:14:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we look back at the price of the first Philips System now,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.26,0:14:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to mention about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.79,0:14:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These were much more popular in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.82,0:14:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,than they were in the US, initially at launch anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.71,0:14:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talking UK price here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the EL3300, which looked much the same as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with inflation works out at 538 pounds today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Still a lot of money, but you know, we're not talking insane amounts of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, we're comparing UK with US price there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and products that are from a few years apart from one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.83,0:14:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't do a direct comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, if we just look at the UK price of the compact cassette system,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.81,0:14:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the el 3300 at the time it launched,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a much more attractive proposition to the average person,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as a tape recorder, than those earlier formats from RCA and 3M.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.70,0:14:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was aimed at a completely different market, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is just designed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.92,0:14:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a simple, easy to use, cassette based audio recorder for voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.97,0:14:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps you could put a bit of music on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.57,0:15:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was mono at the time it was launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas those earlier formats, the 3M and the RCA,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,while she could record your own tapes on these,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from the word go, they had pre-recorded music on them in stereo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were therefore aiming these as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.29,0:15:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a more market crowd a Hi-Fi audiophile enthusiast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.88,0:15:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And that seemed to be the wrong approach
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.56,0:15:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because those people have already got all the records or
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,their reel-to-reel tape recorders, and you then try to encourage them to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.83,0:15:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,get another format with a limited amount of recordings on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh, perhaps a lower quality, well, you just can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean they were expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.02,0:15:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The other people who would be interested
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.32,0:15:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the high-end audio file enthusiast community,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and yeah, they had better formats already that they could have used.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the wrong approach to take Phillips took an approach
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.77,0:15:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from the other end, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.77,0:15:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking for people who hadn't got any kind of tape recorder or
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,had got some basic reel-to-reel machine and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:16:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted something that was more convenient to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly though, based on the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.24,0:16:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there were all those pre-existing formats out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the Philips compact cassette, in the end, wasn't that unique of a device.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there was only one part of this system,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that, they were able to patent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.50,0:16:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or patent something that was unique to the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And can you think what that particular thing is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just take the lid off to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.28,0:16:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, so this is the unique part of the Philips Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.80,0:16:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That was it, not the button, the movable heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.16,0:16:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the head comes up into contact with the cassette,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's engaged, everything else had static heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.34,0:16:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you put the cassette in or the cartridge or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.10,0:16:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you click it into the machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the heads and the pinch roller didn't come up to meet the cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They were already in contact with it from the moment it was put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.13,0:17:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the only part of the cassette that was unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting side note here, footnote. Some kind of note.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1963, Phillips also launched another tape format.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.49,0:17:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if they were trying to hedge their bets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.29,0:17:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't sure whether the compact cassette was going to be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was this one, this came out in 1963 as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is another sort of dictation format.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it comes with these nice little cartridges,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tape gets pulled out of here, and goes into the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.00,0:17:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, it's uh, eighth of an inch wide tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see inside here, we've got the tape
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.17,0:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes in that side take up spool outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the machine automatically threads the tape for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, a more convenient format than strictly open reel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't quite know what the story was with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it was obviously in development at the same time as a cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.26,0:18:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And it came out the same year as the compact cassette from Phillips.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.79,0:18:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd that they bring out two kind of similar ideas in the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.96,0:18:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now of course, it wasn't just Phillips in the early 1960s
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.58,0:18:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who were thinking of producing an easier to use tape-cartridge based system.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like everyone was having a go at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There was loads of different ones in the dictation space particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But these are a few that I've shown over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.90,0:18:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've got the Sanyo micro pack 35,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.70,0:18:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quarter inch tape, stacked on two reels,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.44,0:18:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that was also sold in the US under the Channel Master name, amongst others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.00,0:18:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the "sabermobile".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quarter inch tape again, three inch reels, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.17,0:18:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the these two are perhaps the most interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.92,0:18:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most likely Phillips Compact Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.25,0:18:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If i can get that one out of there...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the Grundig DC International,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, this Sanyo tape cartridge system.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.13,0:18:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too sure if there was a better name than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But uh, that was one that I featured in a video,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.93,0:19:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,where I got a sears branded tape, which looked very similar to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.57,0:19:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the compact cassette, but it wasn't a compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing with this one is that it was basically a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanyo copied the compact cassette, and came out with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Grundig DC International was a little bit more successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've covered the story of the development of this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is kind of an offshoot of the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.26,0:19:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Grundig went off on their own, they weren't gonna join up with Phillips.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.02,0:19:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,(So) They went and did their own thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically copied the cassette design, but came out with this, the DC International.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll put a link to the video, where I go into this in better and greater detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.00,0:19:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But this was an interesting bargaining chip.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This was something that was used in the next section I want to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.17,0:19:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which was really the deal that made the compact cassette successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.72,0:19:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was when Phillips joined up with Sony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.55,0:20:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a bunch of rival, incompatible, and yet, very similar formats on the market
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.10,0:20:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the way you make a successful product.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Phillips wanted the compact cassette to become the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.90,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,single, worldwide agreed standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that reason, they went over to Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.64,0:20:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to Sony to get them on board with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.32,0:20:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the two people attended that meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.11,0:20:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, was Lou Ottens, a gentleman we started off
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.08,0:20:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about at the beginning of this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.92,0:20:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but yes, they wanted Sony to sign up to the compact cassette
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and agree to pay 20 yen for each cassette recorder sold within Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.61,0:20:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sony disagreed with that idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Philips said: Okay, all right,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just charge you six yen for each cassette recorder you sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.79,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, Sony pushed back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason they were able to push back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is because back in 1963, at that IFA Berlin Show,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.72,0:20:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Grundig, the people behind the DC International, had approached Sony.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.59,0:21:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And asked them to co-develop the DC International Cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Sony had said: No we're not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.50,0:21:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But Grundig went ahead, and also wanted still to get Sony on board with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.27,0:21:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Sony were more interested in signing up with the Phillips' system,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.67,0:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but because they were able to say: Well, look, if we don't have to use your cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We could always go with the DC International.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.32,0:21:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're not going to charge us anything if we go with that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So Philips had to agree not to charge any licensing fee for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the compact cassette either if they wanted Sony to adopt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So they were happier to work with Phillips that they were with Grundig.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.84,0:21:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So it all worked out as far as that went, except of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Philips weren't getting any licensing fee for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.14,0:21:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,any compact cassette recorders that Sony went on to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But part of that deal was non-exclusivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that effectively meant that anyone who wanted to,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.84,0:21:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could make a compact cassette recorder or player, I'll not pay Phillips anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.96,0:22:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, yes, it did become a worldwide standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.91,0:22:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't make Phillips rich on licensing fees,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it meant that all those different companies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.60,0:22:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who were involved in the development of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.31,0:22:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the various different cassette recorders and players,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.00,0:22:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,were then all competing against each other to try and make a better product.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.34,0:22:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a open source project.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.09,0:22:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get all these different companies all around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.72,0:22:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in making a better cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that goes all the way back to the people making the tape formulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was what created the cassette boom effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.53,0:22:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Phillips started it off started the ball rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.15,0:22:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But until that day, in 1965 when they met up with Sony,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.00,0:22:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and thrashed out the dealer eventually was finalized in 1966.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.52,0:22:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a little Phillips product that was sold in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.64,0:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The worldwide phenomenon was created really started in 1966.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.32,0:22:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 1967, there were loads of different people making compact cassettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.15,0:22:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there are a lot of data that I've got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.60,0:23:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just go through these quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.00,0:23:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm sure you've got places to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.63,0:23:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But stereo was introduced by Phillips in 1966,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.67,0:23:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dolby B came to the cassette in 1968, as did chrome tape as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.23,0:23:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first Hi-Fi deck really was kind of 1970-71 with the Advent 201.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.24,0:23:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, really not the Philips product,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.28,0:23:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was Advent who really brought out the first deck that played cassettes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.34,0:23:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that people would really consider as a proper Hi-Fi component.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.72,0:23:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the next big event was courtesy of Sony,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.24,0:23:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which I mean, if Sony want on board this one had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.05,0:23:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course that is, the Walkman, 1979.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean everyone says 1979 really, uh, Japan 1979, perhaps uh, US 1980...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know it's expensive, so it's kind of next few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.82,0:23:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, cassette sales tripled over the next four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a product that have been on the market since 1964-ish.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.96,0:24:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And yeah, in 1979, 80, 81, 82, because sales tripled,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.17,0:24:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that's that's really down to this fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.32,0:24:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, as far as we go into stats here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.52,0:24:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the revenue hit the peak for cassettes in the late 1980s.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.12,0:24:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was the best-selling format,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.12,0:24:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,best-selling pre-recorded music format from 1984 to 1992.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.36,0:24:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the best part of a decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.28,0:24:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,CDs the first time that they sold more than cassettes in the US was 1992.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.00,0:24:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So cassettes had a pretty good run at it as the number one format.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.15,0:24:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've just got one final thought about the compact cassette,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.52,0:24:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,something I'd like to mention, because it often gets overlooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.17,0:24:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to do with this in part of a particular area of popular culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.78,0:24:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not to do with music, it's to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.00,0:24:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,computers, and computer games, and programming.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.74,0:24:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the early 1980s, in the UK, if you had a Sinclair Spectrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.36,0:24:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or Commodore 64, and Abstract CPC 464,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.30,0:24:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a Dragger 32 and Oricat Moss...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.16,0:25:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This list could go on, but your primary source of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,loading games and saving programs was to the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.28,0:25:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lot of those kids then went on to create some big programming houses
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that then went on to shape the games that we play
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.37,0:25:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on far more sophisticated devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.84,0:25:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you can see, from all the stuff behind me here,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.06,0:25:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the story of the compact cassette is a little bit more complicated than
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.08,0:25:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps, one line in an obituary that states that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.00,0:25:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Lou Ottens was the inventor of the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.19,0:25:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking nothing away from him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the guy. He was the catalyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.90,0:25:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a chap who went into Phillips one day and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.65,0:25:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,suggested that they work on this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.57,0:25:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is ultimately what created the compact cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.60,0:25:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a lot of pre-existing cassette or cartridge-based formats
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.66,0:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that were assimilated into the design of the cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.72,0:25:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, following the launch of the cassette
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.25,0:25:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there were other formats fell by the wayside.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.40,0:25:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a lot of events that were
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.79,0:25:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the reasons behind the cassette being the success, where the other formats weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.85,0:26:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's really the story of the cassette.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.14,0:26:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So hopefully I've done it a little bit more than
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.17,0:26:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,just put a bit of meat on the bones for you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.32,0:26:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's it for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.80,0:26:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As always, thanks for watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.96,Comments,,0,0,0,,自动字幕整理+翻译：SuperBart 原作者Techmoan发布于2021年3月27日
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.27,0:00:10.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,2021年3月6日，按今天录制时间来说，是十天前
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.46,0:00:15.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Lou Ottens老先生以94岁的高寿过世
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.84,0:00:20.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果大家经常看这个频道的话，你对这件事应该会更加了解
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.58,0:00:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他被大家认为是飞利浦盒式磁带的发明者
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.58,0:00:25.00,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart：{\s1}本视频中，磁带可以有不同的意思，请注意甄别:-P{\s0}\N有人说可以用卡带来避免误会，那就用吧(虽然我从来是没听说过)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.34,0:00:29.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}"发明家"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.06,0:00:31.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想用"发明者"这个词引入这个话题
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.76,0:00:35.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为对我而言，这件事能让我脑子蹦出一堆之前就在想的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.59,0:00:39.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如说，人们在实验室里工作，欣赏着我的发明啥的吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.23,0:00:43.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得飞利浦盒式磁带算是在现代发明出来的吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.84,0:00:47.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是上世纪50年代末，60年代之类的吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:51.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这件事也不完全是他一个人搞
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.82,0:00:54.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，肯定有一下子就能做出来的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.27,0:00:56.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但磁带肯定不是这类
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.92,0:01:01.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有点像是，Steve Jobs发明了iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.19,0:01:03.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，你兴许不会这么说吧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.00,0:01:06.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要去搜索谁发明iPhone的话，你肯定看到的不是一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.15,0:01:10.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你应该看到的是一个团队，经过多年的努力来开发的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:13.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有点像是多个想法的群英荟萃
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.49,0:01:15.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后这改改，那改改啥的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.40,0:01:17.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带也是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.43,0:01:20.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,回到主题，Lou Ottens被认为是盒式磁带的发明者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.75,0:01:25.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我觉得他对这个看法不是很高兴
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.24,0:01:28.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几年前有一个纪录片
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:30.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在那个纪录片也被如此尊称
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.46,0:01:32.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也可以看到，他有点不自在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:33.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，(他说)他是和他的团队一起发明的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.86,0:01:35.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说：好吧，实际上也不完全是我
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.33,0:01:38.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是一个团队，那时有40个人在研发吧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.50,0:01:41.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拿出卡带的这位是设计师
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.01,0:01:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有工程师啥的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.44,0:01:46.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但事实也不是，如果没有Lou Ottens在工作时候想出这个主意
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:49.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后在那说"兄弟们，我们应该在这方面开展工作"的话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.80,0:01:51.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦公司就不搞这个玩意了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:53.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但就像其他的"发明者"一样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.97,0:01:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是在飞利浦里，磁带项目的发起者吧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:03.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但又说回来，就算在飞利浦之外，依然有很多人在实现这个想法
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，在飞利浦的盒式磁带研发之前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,市面上已经有很多的类似产品了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本思路还都差不多
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:17.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟这个想法也不是从石头缝里蹦出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.18,0:02:23.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种将其放在盒子，或者卡带的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:25.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是为了在使用磁带时，不用将其手动缠在机器上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他们研发的时候，也融合了一些先前产品的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:35.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而那些东西也算是奠定了飞利浦盒式磁带中的一些基本元素
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:37.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个东西确实成功了，但那些第一批尝试这个想法的人呢
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:40.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们真正证实了这个想法是能实现的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.61,0:02:44.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在呢，我们来看看在飞利浦盒式磁带出现之前，有怎样的东西吧
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.61,0:02:50.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}飞利浦盒式磁带之前研发的盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:55.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了能更好理解先前产品对盒式卡带设计的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:58.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们得先知道飞利浦盒式卡带是在什么时候研发的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:01.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦盒式卡带本身是在1963年8月底向公众发布的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.62,0:03:04.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是说，开发是在其之前的事情了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,据我读过的资料，开发应该是从1960-1961年开始的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:13.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我们假设是从1960年开始的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:17.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时Ottens先生跟他在飞利浦的同事们说
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:19.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们应该在这个方向工作
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:23.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既然大家不乐意将磁带缠在开盘机上
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:28.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们来点简单的，将磁带放在一合适的卡带里，以简便使用
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:33.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，飞利浦在开盘机生产方面，有很厚的历史积淀
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:35.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟，盒式磁带比起开盘机，就是小了一些
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:39.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是呢，他们当时有很多的开盘机在售
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:42.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，他们自己研发出来的两台类似机器
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.56,0:03:45.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,确实对飞利浦盒式卡带的影响很大
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:51.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个是这个，上面的商标是由Stella生产的Stellaphone
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个是由飞利浦生产的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.72,0:03:58.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,该机器使用3英寸的开盘带录制，首发于1961
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:04:01.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里有个更早发行的版本
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.23,0:04:06.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是老版发行更多，促使他们继续开发盒式卡带
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.31,0:04:08.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,估计是从中搞到更多经费吧
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:10.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本身这个东西就很成功
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:14.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这台机器是使用三英寸开盘带的，我这有一些
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:19.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是单独缠在一起的，而不是从机器上拿下来的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:24.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然，当时已经有很多机器使用三英寸开盘带了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一个飞利浦自家产品，采用了装在盒子里的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个产品可以往前推到1957年末到1958年初
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:40.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这玩意还挺沉的，全金属机身
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我得想一下这个机器的序列号
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.46,0:04:45.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到了，EL3581
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一个飞利浦牌的听写机
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:52.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看上去和其他的开盘机没啥区别
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，这台机器用的是这个东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.40,0:04:59.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,装在盒子里的三英寸开盘带
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.60,0:05:00.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你买回来就是这样装好的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.65,0:05:02.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你不用再往里面放一个了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:04.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然你也能打开盒子，将里面的磁带拿出来，放在其他机器上用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:07.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得，这也许是飞利浦生产的第一种“盒式卡带”吧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.13,0:05:11.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,十分原始，就塑料盒里开俩洞
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:14.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,里面放俩卷筒，上面再缠上磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:18.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过他们说，这么设计是为了“方便快速放置磁带”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:20.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就将其放在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:23.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是1957年飞利浦生产的"盒式卡带"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.68,0:05:27.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在飞利浦盒式卡带出现前，出品的一款产品
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:32.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而有一些其他的产品，对磁带有更加直接的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.98,0:05:34.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我拿出几个举例
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.91,0:05:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}两种盒式卡带的融合
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:42.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好的，这个更像，基本就是"盒式卡带"了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:44.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟......好吧，这不是飞利浦的那个:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.24,0:05:47.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是RCA录音卡带，里面是磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.55,0:05:50.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里有一个宣传片
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,应该是当时拍摄的吧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.46,0:05:54.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这个视频在油管上有
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是1958年录的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:06:03.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进而，你读到很多的关于RCA录音卡带的资料，都说是1958年出的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:10.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而不是这样，像很多东西一样，这个宣传片是在产品出品前录的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:10.09,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart举例：我校联通宽带(西电联通手机信号很差) David大叔的Amiga视频
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:13.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且是很久之前，虽然RCA研发这个产品很久了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:16.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但正如你在很多关于RCA研发过程的视频中看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.41,0:06:21.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们看样子并没有成功发布这款产品
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.14,0:06:26.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不知为何，开发周期很长，但他们不能很好地将其推向市场
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:29.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,貌似最后阶段，他们翻车了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.46,0:06:31.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个也是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:36.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开发了那么多年，直到1959年才发布
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.53,0:06:38.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以说是软发布了:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.53,0:06:38.28,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：软发布是指在有限或不做推广的情况下新产品上线
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:42.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,估计这玩意出品的时候，RCA只有两个机器
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:47.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而他们还是吸引了其他人，比如贝尔公司，和他们在这方面合作
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:49.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得和他们合作的公司还不少
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.78,0:06:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，你会看到其他公司出品的机器
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:54.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得RCA并没有一直支持这款产品
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们将其出售了，有点像是出售股份啥的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:07:00.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们将这个产品的产权卖给那些投资的人
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后RCA就说：“我们对这个产品没啥信心”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:05.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好吧，真就摸着石头过河呗:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:09.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这到底是个嘛玩意？兴许我应该从这里开始讲
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带宽四分之一英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.28,0:07:13.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和飞利浦用的磁带规格一样
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:17.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是双声道，有些机器能自动翻带
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:22.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且音质很不错，挺好的介质
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:24.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我录过一些示例视频，音质很好
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:29.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是1959出品的产品，在当时绝对很出色
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:32.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦坐在那里就想：“我们也搞个这样的磁带”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.19,0:07:36.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这可以说是磁带了，可惜市场上不成功
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:41.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得，一部分可以归咎于RCA对自己家产品缺乏热情吧
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:44.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,另外一方面，就是价格问题了，我们现在看看价格
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.19,0:07:46.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们来看看，之前我收集过了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.49,0:07:53.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当年卖300美元，考虑通货膨胀的话，放现在得是2700美元
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:58.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这价格，绝对不可能是大众化产品啊，价格太贵了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:01.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个产品有很多技术革新
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.17,0:08:03.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如说，头一回在磁带上有四个音轨
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.02,0:08:09.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之后很多人都做四轨磁带，家用开盘机上也普及了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:13.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且，他们还将带速降到了每秒3.75英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:17.16,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,而在当时，很多磁带录音机的带速是每秒7.5英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:22.13,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,人们就想：好家伙，这磁带带速3.75，上面有四轨道，音质行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:19.51,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1446,814)}*对于音乐磁带来说
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:24.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们后来证实，音质确实行
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:31.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一部分原因在于3M为了配套该项目，开发了一种更好类型的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.28,0:08:33.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没错，早期磁带十分粗糙，要想用的话
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:37.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你走带的速度得快，兴许只能放两个轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:39.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，为保证在四轨，带速将至一半的前提下
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:41.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,音质依然能够很好，没有嘶嘶声
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.92,0:08:45.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你得为这方面的市场，搞出一种新的磁带配方
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,3M公司当时开发磁带已有多年
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:51.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们对该产品随时推向市场十分关注
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.00,0:08:53.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟已经有了这个产品，将来推出后肯定是热门产品
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:57.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以3M对这个产品意气蓬发，不过RCA意兴阑珊
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:09:00.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这时，3M算是受够了RCA的不作为
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:05.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们就想发行自己的盒式磁带，但是还不能叫盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:08.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们就把这玩意叫做卡带吧，按卡带看待吧
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:10.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们这就推出了他们自己研发的盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.58,0:09:15.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他们受够RCA做事情太笨，而且兴致不高
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.80,0:09:20.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，就是这个了，3M的盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.29,0:09:22.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在1959年展示过这个东西
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.59,0:09:26.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后是60-61年，最终在1962年12月发布
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.72,0:09:29.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们也证实了一点
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:33.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在对RCA动火前，应该意识到推出一个新格式不是一件简单的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.75,0:09:37.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好吧，这个3M Revere 卡带又是个啥玩意？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:41.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个使盒式磁带的诞生成为可能
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这两个上面的缺口基本相同
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.00,0:09:47.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带速一样，都是1.875英寸每秒
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.87,0:09:50.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带宽八分之一英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:54.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而区别呢，当飞利浦的磁带发布的时候，是单声道的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.39,0:09:58.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了播放两面的音轨，你半途得换面
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:00.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一面只有一个音轨
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:05.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个呢，磁带上也是两个音轨
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:10.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个是双声道，所以这个开盘带更大
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:13.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，飞利浦的盒式磁带上将来也会有
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这个呢，磁带会从卡带里扽出来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:19.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本上，里面的磁带就是一卷
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.20,0:10:23.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后磁带被卷进机器里，磁带顺势经过磁头
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.44,0:10:25.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样，磁带上的两轨正好可以弄成立体声
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:29.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是一种音乐介质了，他们的意思是，立体声音乐介质
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:33.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个东西能让盒式磁带的出现成为可能(的原因是)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他能够证明，磁带可以在那样的速度下运行
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:38.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且质量(音质)也足够好
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:40.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些都是3M能够做出这样的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.15,0:10:47.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些开发出这类介质的人们，也在开发一种新的降噪系统
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.39,0:10:52.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以适配存于带速为每秒1.875英寸磁带上的音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:56.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这可以说是飞利浦盒式磁带的原型了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.21,0:11:00.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个也算一个，左边那个是外观
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:01.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,右面的是里面的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.87,0:11:05.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这俩一结合，就成这个了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:11.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本算吧:-P 实际上，抛开那两个，当时市场上还有其他格式
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:12.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我这里没有实机，我这里就给大家
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.93,0:11:17.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,展示一些从Museum of Obsolete Media收集来的图片
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.04,0:11:19.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你现在看到的是 Minifon Attaché
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.82,0:11:22.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1959年首次展示
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.00,0:11:26.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是在1960由德国汉堡公司Protona发布
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.80,0:11:32.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们主要生产间谍录音机，打字机或是微型录音机
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.94,0:11:35.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我搞来了他们生产的有线录音机
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:38.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里，他们使用的是6.25毫米(0.25英寸)的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这绝对是和飞利浦的盒式磁带长得很相似啊
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个发布于1960年，正好是飞利浦开始研发盒式磁带的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我敢肯定，飞利浦一定知道Minifon Attaché的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟他们开发的时候，不是与世隔绝的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:03.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们一定寻找过已在市场上存在过的产品，然后在其基础上改进
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:13.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有人说，他们特意注意了RCA的卡带以及3M的卡带
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:17.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我敢确定，他们也在注意 Minifon Attaché
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:20.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个估计更加著名一些
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这个呢，应该没几个人听说过吧:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.56,0:12:28.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在也不是很著名，因为这个在当时市场上也不是很成功
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.72,0:12:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个介质呢，是八分之一英寸宽的磁带，在此之前还没有呢
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:44.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种1/8英寸宽磁带的质量很好，飞利浦盒式磁带上将会使用这种磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:49.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦当时就在找，这些卡带带里面都有什么呢
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要是他们借鉴Minifon Attaché
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:12:54.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用0.25英寸宽的磁带，成品体积会很可观
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.84,0:12:58.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要是使用八分之一英寸宽的磁带的话，成品会更小些
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.83,0:13:01.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本上，最终就会成为这样
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.83,0:13:05.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是带速每秒3.75英寸，0.25英寸宽的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:08.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是带速每秒1.875英寸，八分之一英寸宽的磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.40,0:13:11.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是磁带粗细所带来的区别
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:14.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一句话，磁带的变细是一个很大的技术进步
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.40,0:13:17.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是飞利浦的盒式磁带能够做出来的一个重要方面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:22.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在，我再谈谈为啥这玩意的售价，让其在市场上不成功
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:26.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以在1962年12月，他们进行了试售
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.19,0:13:32.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,录音设备或播放设备需要花费450美元
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:39.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1962年的450美元，算上通胀，现在的3900美元
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:42.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带很便宜，但机器真的是花费颇多
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:44.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，这是其未能成功的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:52.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，飞利浦的目标是将这些磁带用在一个简易些的设备上
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.75,0:13:55.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样的话，新设备的生产成本更低
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:59.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因而，磁带真的很便宜
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.01,0:14:04.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们看看第一部飞利浦的盒式磁带播放机的话，是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.79,0:14:10.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相比首发地美国来说，磁带在欧洲更加流行
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.71,0:14:13.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我们说的是英国售价
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:17.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这台EL3300，基本上长成这样
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:21.19,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,算上通货膨胀，在今天售卖538英镑
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:24.64,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,虽然价格还是可观，但也并非贵得遥不可及
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:24.64,Chinese Up,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1520,840)}1几尼=1.05英镑
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:27.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我们比较英美两地的售价，以及两地发行的产品
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:31.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但两地发行的产品毕竟时间啥的有所不同，所以没法直接比较
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:35.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是呢，单看英国这里磁带机的售价
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.81,0:14:42.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在EL3300发布的时候，显然，对普通人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:47.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相比RCA和3M搞的那俩，这是一个价格上更合适的磁带录音机
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.70,0:14:50.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过，这个面向的是一个完全不同的市场
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:51.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟，这个是被设计用来录制人声的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.92,0:14:57.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,简单易用的磁带录音机
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.97,0:14:59.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,兴许录些RickRoll也没问题:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.97,0:14:59.57,Comments,,0,0,0,,SuperBart：或者是一些广播电台播放的歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.57,0:15:02.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这玩意首发的时候，只有单声道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:07.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而那些更早的介质，RCA的和3M的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:09.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管也能自行在磁带上录音
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:14.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们预灌录的音乐都是双声道的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:21.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们面向的，主要是发烧音乐爱好者
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.88,0:15:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们看样子走错方向了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.56,0:15:29.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为这些人大多已经有录在开盘带上的音乐了，你再让他们去
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.83,0:15:33.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,购买其他的介质，专辑数量也不多
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:37.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,兴许质量还更差，谁会冒这个险呢:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:39.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟，这些东西的价格摆在那了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.02,0:15:46.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些有可能入坑HiFi的人，已经拥有那些他们使用过的更好介质了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:51.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们失败的尝试，促使飞利浦从另一面市场入手
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.77,0:15:55.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们面向的是没有任何磁带机，或是有
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:16:01.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很基本的开盘机，想要找个更方便使用的机器
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:07.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有趣的是，尽管已经有了很多的基于磁带的媒介了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.36,0:16:13.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦的盒式磁带呢，最终也不是一个那么独特的介质
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:19.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得，整个机器只有一个部分可以申请专利
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.50,0:16:24.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或是对于磁带来说，可以算是独特到可以申请专利了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:27.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你觉得具体会是哪个部分呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:30.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把盖子拿掉，给你们演示一下
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.28,0:16:35.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好的，这就是飞利浦盒式磁带机的独特部分了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.80,0:16:41.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是这个，不是按钮，而是可动的磁头
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.16,0:16:45.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁头自行移动，和磁带接触的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:49.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦的磁带机是这样的时候，其他的都是固定磁头
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.34,0:16:54.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你将盒式磁带放进机器，打开开关的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:58.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是磁头和转轮并没有弹出，和磁带接触
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:01.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从盒式磁带放进的一刻起，他们就和磁带接触上了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.13,0:17:06.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以飞利浦的磁带机，也就这点新颖
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:11.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我插一句
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:16.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1963年，飞利浦发行了另一种磁带格式
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.49,0:17:21.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,(不知是不是他们怕盒式磁带不成功，想两边下注)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是这个，也是1963年发布
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:30.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个也是给听写机用的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:33.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还附带一个挺小，挺耐人的卡带
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带从这里扽出来，被拽进机器
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.00,0:17:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这个磁带也是八分之一英寸宽的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:46.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们看看里面，这边的磁带被拽出
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:49.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,机器自动将磁带给你传进那面的盒子里
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:53.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自然，这个比直接开盘，自己缠磁带方便多了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:56.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我对此设备的开发背后的故事，了解不多
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:59.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得，这玩意和磁带的开发是同时的啊
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.26,0:18:04.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后还和盒式磁带一样，都由飞利浦在同一年发布
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.79,0:18:08.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们同一年发行两款类似产品，真是奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.10,0:18:12.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}还有一些尝试
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.96,0:18:15.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，上世纪60年代，不止飞利浦想要
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.58,0:18:19.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开发一种简易易用的磁带-卡带介质
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:21.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看样子，所有人都想在此方面插一腿
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:24.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时特别在听写机方面，有好多不同的设备
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:26.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里我展示一些我这几年展示过的设备
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.90,0:18:33.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是三洋的Micro Pack 35，0.25宽的磁带，卷在两个滚轮上
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.44,0:18:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和其他的一样，这个在美国在Channel Master品牌下销售
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.00,0:18:39.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是“Sabermobile”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:43.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是0.25宽的磁带，应该是3寸开盘吧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.17,0:18:48.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来这俩就有些意思了，也是最像飞利浦盒式磁带的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.25,0:18:49.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,等我将其拿出来……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:52.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个是 Grundig DC International
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:56.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这个是三洋的磁带-卡带系统
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.13,0:18:58.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也不知他们有没有当时给这玩意起个更好的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:00.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过呢，关于这个，我在那期视频里展示过
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.93,0:19:07.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我是得到了一些Sears牌子的磁带，看上去像磁带，但并不是磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:10.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这玩意基本上就是个复制品啊
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:14.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三洋抄袭了飞利浦磁带的创意，然后搞出来这个
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:19.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而 The Grundig DC International 更加成功些
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:21.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我之前讲过这个的开发历程了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:24.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这算是飞利浦盒式磁带开发时候的一点小插曲吧
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.26,0:19:27.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Grundig 自己开发去了，他们不想和飞利浦一起干
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.02,0:19:28.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以他们自己搞去了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:33.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本复制了飞利浦磁带的设计，就搞出来个这个
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我做过一期视频，详细介绍这个东西，回来去看看啊
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.00,0:19:41.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过这里，我来讲一段有趣的一段议价故事
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:45.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,下一部分，我主要说的就是这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.17,0:19:49.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这件事，促使了磁带的成功
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.72,0:19:52.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是飞利浦和索尼谈合作的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.74,0:19:56.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}毁誉参半的交易？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.55,0:20:02.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要想让你的产品成功，搞个和竞争对手
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.10,0:20:05.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,十分相似，但互不兼容的竞品是不行的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:10.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦想让他们的盒式磁带成为这个领域的单一，全球公认标准
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:15.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为此，他们飞到日本，和索尼谈判，想和他们合作
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.32,0:20:17.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有两个人参与了那个会议
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.11,0:20:21.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其中有一位，正是我在视频开头说的 Lou Ottens
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.92,0:20:26.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论如何，他们想让索尼签下磁带协议
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:33.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并同意飞利浦在每一台在日本销售的磁带录音机上抽成20日元
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.61,0:20:35.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,索尼回绝了这个想法
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:42.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后飞利浦说：得，每台机器抽成6日元吧
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.79,0:20:44.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,索尼又一次回绝了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:46.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而索尼能够拒绝他们的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1963年的柏林国际电子消费品展览会上
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.72,0:20:56.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生产 DC International 的 Grundig 公司找到了索尼
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.59,0:21:01.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想让他们一起合作开发 DC International 磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,索尼说：我们不感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.50,0:21:08.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但 Grundig 没有罢休，还是想和索尼合作
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.27,0:21:13.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,索尼现在对和飞利浦的磁带签约更感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.67,0:21:22.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是他们也可以说：我们可以不用你们的，用Grundig公司的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.32,0:21:25.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们和他签约的话，他们可不会抽成啊
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:32.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦要想让索尼接受的话，他们也得同意不向索尼收取授权费
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.25,0:21:35.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样，索尼和飞利浦合作，较Grundig来得更加愉快
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.84,0:21:39.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,目前进展一切顺利，除了一点
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:46.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦并没有对索尼生产的飞利浦盒式磁带录音机抽成
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:50.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但协议中的部分条款是非排他性的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:53.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这实际上意味着，任何想做
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.84,0:21:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦盒式磁带录音机或播放器的人，他们不必给飞利浦任何东西
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.96,0:22:01.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，飞利浦的磁带成了全球标准
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.91,0:22:05.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然并没有让飞利浦收授权费，赚到很多钱
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:12.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这意味着那些参与开发过许多不同的卡带播放/录音机的公司
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.00,0:22:15.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都会尽力生产更好的产品，进而相互竞争
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.34,0:22:18.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有点像是开源计划了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.09,0:22:22.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样，全球各地不同的公司都参与进来，生产更好的盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:26.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一切都是从那些研发更好磁带的人开始说起
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:31.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这也是促使了磁带繁荣的开始
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.53,0:22:34.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没错，飞利浦开了头，之后就是滚雪球那样的繁荣了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.15,0:22:37.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但直到1965年和索尼的会见
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.00,0:22:43.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以及1966年才结束的和其他公司的谈判之后
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.52,0:22:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦的产品在欧洲的销量并不好
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.64,0:22:52.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全球的盒式磁带流行是从1966年开始的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.32,0:22:56.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到了1967年，好多不同的公司都在生产盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.15,0:22:58.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，我这里有很多数据
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.60,0:23:01.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们快速过一下，因为你们八成已经知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.63,0:23:05.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦在1966年首先发明了双声道盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.67,0:23:11.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,杜比B降噪和铬带是1967年发明的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.23,0:23:17.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一个Hifi卡座是1970-71左右出现的Advent 201
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.24,0:23:19.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,再说一遍，不是飞利浦
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.28,0:23:26.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是Advent首先发布了人们公认的HiFi卡座
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.72,0:23:30.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,盒式磁带历史的下一个重要时刻是索尼创造的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.24,0:23:33.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，如果索尼和飞利浦真合作的话，估计早就发生了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.05,0:23:37.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,话说回来，1979年，磁带随身听诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:43.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数人说的1979年是日本首发，美国得1980年吧……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:45.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但一开始很贵，所以火起来是接下几年的事情了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.82,0:23:50.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过，盒式磁带的销量在接下了的四年翻了三番
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:56.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没错，这可是1964年上市的产品啊
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.96,0:24:02.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，79-82年，销量翻了三倍
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.17,0:24:04.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这件事确实很重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.32,0:24:07.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，再接着看数据呢
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.52,0:24:11.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,磁带销量在八十年代末期达至顶峰
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.12,0:24:13.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是销量最好的音乐格式了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.12,0:24:17.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从1984年到1992年，都是销量最好的提前灌制好的音乐格式
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.36,0:24:19.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以是磁带的黄金十年了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.28,0:24:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1992年，在美国，CD的销量头一回超过了磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.00,0:24:30.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为销量第一的介质，磁带的成绩十分不错
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.94,0:24:33.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,186)}...0010001001...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.15,0:24:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于磁带，我又想到了最后一出
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.52,0:24:38.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得得提一句，因为这件事经常被忽视
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.17,0:24:42.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这件事和某些地区的流行文化相关
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.78,0:24:47.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这件事和音乐无关，是和电脑，电脑游戏，以及编程相关
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.74,0:24:58.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在八十年代早期的英国，如果你有如下所列的电脑(名单还能更长)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.35,0:25:05.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过你加载游戏，保存程序的话，你主要的介质就是磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.28,0:25:10.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其中有一些孩子，创建了一些大型软件公司
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:15.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后在更加复杂的平台上，塑造出当代游戏的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.84,0:25:18.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如你所见，由我后面这么多的史料
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.06,0:25:21.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,飞利浦盒式磁带的故事远比那条写着
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.08,0:25:26.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“Lou Ottens是飞利浦盒式磁带发明者”的讣告要复杂那么一点吧
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.19,0:25:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,抛开他的其他一些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:29.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就是那个伟大的人，他就是磁带出现的催化剂
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.90,0:25:34.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有一天，就是他跑进飞利浦办公室，建议团队在这个想法上工作
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.57,0:25:37.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最终，造就了我们所熟知的盒式磁带
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.60,0:25:41.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但之前也有很多已经存在的盒式磁带，或卡带类型的格式
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.66,0:25:45.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们的某些设计融入了飞利浦的盒式磁带之中
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.72,0:25:50.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，随着飞利浦盒式磁带的发布，好多其他格式衰落了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.40,0:25:57.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也有好多东西，说明了为啥只有飞利浦的盒式磁带行，其他的不行
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.85,0:26:00.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本上，磁带的故事就是这样了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.14,0:26:04.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,希望我这期视频，不仅仅是在一些常识上扩充了一点东西罢了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.32,0:26:05.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过本期视频就是这样了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.80,0:26:07.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一如既往，感谢大家收看:-)
